sentences: Martin Kenneavy (died c. 1890) was an Irish piper.
Kenneavy or Kinneavy is a very rare Irish surname, found exclusively in County Galway in the mid-19th century.
Kenneavy served for six years in either the 9th Queen's Royal Lancers or the 12th Royal Lancers.
"In 1887, after a long absence from my native land, I heard him play in Gibney's tavern, at the top of Knockmaroon hill, Phoenix Park, and from him I picked up some fine tunes."
Kenneavy died in Newcastle upon Tyne, England, about 1890.
